item.title: FORWARD DMV Showcase : The Loft is Back!
item.dc:creator: user
item.content:encoded:
We’re thrilled to announce that our FORWARD DMV Showcase this Friday, April 11th is going to take place at Union Arts DC, otherwise known as the 411 Loft!

411 New York Ave NE DC

It’s been impossible finding a venue that has the same intimate atmosphere and cozy vibe that the Loft provided us for so many years. We figured we would just stop searching and do whatever it takes to get back to our favorite spot in DC. THE WAIT IS OVER, FORWARD FAMILY! We can’t begin to express how excited we are for this Friday. Bring your dancing shoes and don’t plan on going home til LATE.
Each year, before FORWARD kicks off we host a locals showcase. Locals are the foundation of our community. They inspire us, propel our scene, get and keep the party going. On this special night, we’re happy to be hosting a grip of locals that are all doing proper things in pushing our scene FORWARD and broadening our perspective on dance music.
FRIDAY.APRIL.11.2014 | 21+ | 10PM - LATE | $10  *FREE for FORWARD Pass Holders* http://www.forwarddc.com/passes.html Don’t Miss Out on Any of the Official FORWARD 2014 Preview Events…

item.title: Forward Preview Event: Amir Alexander
item.dc:creator: user
item.content:encoded:
FORWARD Preview Event Announcement: A Tribute to Frankie Knuckles and Celebration of the Underground, featuring Amir Alexander.
 
 
FORWARD and Bump ‘n Grind are happy to welcome Amir Alexander to Zeba for his DC Debut. Amir currently lives in Berlin, but is and has been a mainstay and proponent of the Chicago underground house scene for years. As proponents of the underground for over 10 years in DC thinking through our Frankie Knuckles tribute and FORWARD’s perspective theme, we couldn’t ask for a better figure/guide to help us celebrate Frankie’s legacy than Amir.Frankie pioneered the underground in Chicago, creating a scene and lifestyle for thousands where the literally wasn’t one. He created a refuge for those that walked on the fringe, those that needed a safe place to express themselves emotionally/physically for hours on end. Amir is carrying that torch, carrying that flame and will be showcasing and juxtaposing the Chicago underground’s legacy and perspective via three turntables for our beloved DC community. Bring your open mind and heart. Wear those shoes and duds that inspire you to move and prepare to shimmy your way across that baby powdered dance floor as we welcome Amir Alexander to DC. FREE for FORWARD 2014 Pass holders. FB Event » Here «

item.title: Forward DC 2014 Preview: KAHN (Extended Set) @ Tropicalia
item.dc:creator: user
item.content:encoded:
As an official preview event for FORWARD 2014, we are pleased to announce KAHN (Extended Set),Encryption B2B Refugee, and Jett Chandon Thursday, April 17 at Tropicalia. Born and raised in the bass Mecca that is Bristol, Kahn is viewed by many as one of the best purveyor’s of bass oriented music. With releases on labels as diverse as Deep Medi, Idle hands, Punch drunk and Hotline. His cuts span grime, dubstep and dancehall. He’s an artist with a unique ability to tap into the roots of bass as well as lead it into unchartered territory, hence why he’s the perfect act to play a rare extended set showcasing his perspective on bass music at this year’s FORWARD bass preview event. Kahn will be joined by 3 of our favorite local selectors; Encryption, Refugee, and Jett Chandon for what promises to be a great opportunity to experience the kind of vibes you can expect from FORWARD 2014.

Check out this mix Kahn recently laid down for mixmag.

2001 14th ST NW DC (Lower Level) 21+ | 9PM - 2AM | $10 *FREE with FORWARD 2014 Festival Pass*

item.title: Amir Alexander
item.dc:creator: user
item.content:encoded:
I mix records...... I make tracks..... I dance to good underground club music. I have a crew: "The Vanguard Crew." This is our website: vanguardsound.com
A Dj. since 93. A producer since 98. A true student of the music/culture. Amir founded Vanguard Sound in February 2006. After making his presence felt in the Chicago club scene via a meteoric rise culminating a Dj watch feature in Chicago’s 5 magazine, he completely disappeared and went beneath the underground to focus solely on advancing his production skills. Soon after linking up with G. Marcell and Hakim Murphy he began to release gritty tracks that have been charted and played by underground Dj’s world wide. His fourth release was the sleeper classic “Experience ep” a 4 tracker with Amir on side a, and G. Marcell on side b. Encouraged by the feedback, Amir then submitted tracks to New York city’s Plan B Recordings. The rest is history as they say....... Recording under the name Amir Alexander and the pseudonym Guerrilla Soul! this cat strives to bring a raw and gritty modern spin on classic Detroit, Chicago, and New York underground sounds.

item.title: Kahn
item.dc:creator: user
item.content:encoded:
Hailing from Bristol (U.K) and having grown up immersed in the city's renowned culture of sound systems, punk rock and hip hop; Kahn is at the forefront of the new wave of Bristol producers and DJs.
From his first vinyl releases in 2011 on cult record label Punch Drunk Records to his more recent cuts on Mala's Deep Medi label, Kahn has established himself as one of the most diverse producers of his generation.
His production style tends to draw influence from dub reggae, early 2000's grime, digital dancehall, UK steppers and music from across the 140bpm spectrum. As part of the Young Echo collective, Kahn has also explored other areas of electronic music and incorporates his own vocals and instrumentation into his sound.
As a DJ, Kahn keeps true to the traditions of sound system culture with sets full of dubplates and versions. Whether performing solo as Kahn, alongside fellow grime producer and DJ Neek or as Gorgon Sound (dub and dancehall project also with Neek), it's always a dubplate and vinyl operation.
As well as releases and affiliations with a number of respected record labels, Kahn also runs his own imprint with Neek, Bandulu Records. Since forming at the beginning of 2012, the record label has gone on to showcase the darker forms of instrumental Grime permeating from Bristol's current underground scene, with limited runs of heavyweight vinyl and hand screen-printed artwork.

item.title: Robert Manos
item.dc:creator: user
item.content:encoded:
Robert Manos is a New York based singer and musician who has collaborated on Techno, Drum and Bass and Deep House releases with Jesper Dahlbäck, Seba, Terry Lee Brown Junior, Paradox, Hugg and Pepp, John Dahlbäck, Charles Webster and Alexi Delano.
He spent his early years in Germany, Kenya and Tanzania before moving to New York as a teenager. His musical background is shaped by many influences, including 70’s Soul, R&B, New Wave, Dancehall Reggae and Classical Music. He began recording bits and pieces on a 4 track recorder using primarily drum machines,synths and electric bass and gradually began to add his voice to these recordings.
Working as a bass player and background vocalist with various bands and projects, Robert began to develop his own style which can only be described as a mixture of everything he was exposed to, and as a way of trying to define the realities of living many lives in different worlds, the distance this can cause between people but also the sense of being connected to everything but at times lost to yourself.
In 2002, Robert began collaborating on projects with Jesper Dahlbäck and Sebastian Ahrenberg in Stockholm (Sweden), starting with the deep house track “My World”. The first full album from Robert Manos called “Angel Road” was co-produced by Jesper Dahlbäck and Sebastian Ahrenberg as well and was recorded at Globe Studios in Stockholm. Additional recording was done at Ingaro Studios in Budapest (Hungary) and a certain small apartment facing east high above 7th ave, New York (USA).

item.title: Paradox
item.dc:creator: user
item.content:encoded:
In recent years he has championed a new sub-genre of drum and bass known as drumfunk, which focuses on either finding obscure breakbeats or re-sampling much used drum-and-bass breakbeats from their original source and transforming them into constantly shifting drum patterns, noticeably different from traditional drum and bass. He also records a duo with producer Nucleus. He also has regularly collaborated with artist Seba.
Paradox also records under the pseudonym Alaska. From 1994 to 1996, Pandya went by the alias Brown in collaboration with Rhymeside (Scott Williams), DJ Trax (David Davies) and Dangerman, which is another alias from Davies. Under the artist name of DMR Pandya released tracks as Paradox & DMR on the label Certificate 18 in 1998. Pandya runs four record labels: Paradox Music, Esoteric, Outsider, and Arctic Music. He also ran the labels Mob Handed, Stronghold Records and Offset Recordings together with Davies from 1994 to 1997. Those labels are inactive, which means that there are no more records released on them.
Paradox released his first full-length album Musician as Outsider in 2000 on Reinforced Records as single artist. Both the CD and LP releases have ten tracks on them, but the CD version had a bonus CD with live PA-footage from Paradox's 2000 tour. There was a special Japan version of the CD, released by Sony Japan, which featured changed patterns, different run times and the bonus-track "The Unspoken Divide". In 2002 the second Paradox album, again on Reinforced Records came out, called What You Don't Know. The LP version features ten tracks and the double CD release has 12 tracks on CD 1 and video footage from the 2002 live tour on CDVD (CD 2).
In 2004, the album The Esoteric Funk by Nucleus & Paradox was released on Reinforced Records. Nucleus' real name is Dave Sims. Sims and Pandya had released a CD album before in 1997 which is called Noise & Paradox – Transmograpfication. At that time Simms went by the name "Noise".
Paradox released the first CD Seba & Paradox – Beats Me on his label Paradox Music in 2006 featuring tracks from Seba, Paradox and Seba & Paradox collaborations.
In 2007, Paradox released the first CD on his label Outsider called Paradox Presents: The Age Of Outsiders featuring selected tracks from all releases on Outsider. CD 1 was mixed by Nucleus and CD 2 was mixed by DJ Trax.
July 2006 saw the 100th release of Paradox. On this occasion the 12" release was a special red vinyl featuring remixes of the Paradox-tracks "The Unspoken Divide" and "Give the Drummer Some".
In collaboration with Bill Laswell and Herbie Hancock, Paradox is featured on the album Method Of Defiance – Inamorata on the label Ohm Resistance with two tracks. While the track "Panepha" has Paradox programmed the drums, Hancock plays the keyboard and Laswell the bass. The track "Humanoid" has Paradox, again drum programmer, Toshinori Kondo on the trumpet, Bernie Worrell (Parliament Funkadelic) on the keyboards and Laswell as usual on the bass. The album was released in 2007.
Altogether Pandya released circa 320 tracks on 42 labels from 1993 to 2008 using different aliases and in collaboration with many artists including Nucleus/Noise, Volcov, Alaska/DMR, Seba, DJ Trax, Marc De Clive-Lowe and Subject 13.
He also did remixes not only of his own tracks but from artists including Deep Blue, Resound, Shobha Gurtu, LTJ Bukem, Materia, Ultra-Violet, James Hardway, Kirsty Hawkshaw, Ill Logic & Raf, Duo Infernale, DJ Trax, NXS, Boom Boom Satellites and Justice.

item.title: FORWARD 2014 Preview Event: CLOUDWATCH 20th Anniversary Celebration
item.dc:creator: user
item.content:encoded: As an official preview event for FORWARD 2014 we are honored to present the 20th Anniversary Celebration of CLOUDWATCH on Saturday May 3rd at Blind Whino a recently rehabilitated Church in SW DC. The all ages event will feature over 15 performing artists, 3 Sound Systems, Visuals, Food Trucks and Bliss. Early Bird Tickets and more information can be purchased here. The event is free for FORWARD pass holders and children under 10. Talent to date, MORE TBA: Original Cloudwatch/Sonic Soul artists -  DJ LoveGrove, Infinity, K Ravi(Live), Graham S as well as: Aligning Minds (Live), De Rigueur (Timewarp Records/ Kraak Records NYC), DJ Who, Slant, Pete Welsch (Fatback), Thomas Blondet (Rhythm and Culture Recordings), Adam T Rush, Joe L, A-Deal, Kevin Yost (Live and Improvised Chill Out Set), David, VJ Kaboom (Klip.tv), Capsaicin… For those that grew up on the East Coast, CloudWatch was a staple from 1994 - 2000 dedicated to the sounds of ambient, dub, down-tempo, funk, soul, minimal techno, atmospheric drum n bass, experimental electronic, ethnic world influence, and deep house. The event brought all those styles together as the main focus, rather than be relegated to the “chill out” room. In addition, CloudWatch celebrated the multi-media aspect of underground sub-culture — inviting artists to create decor, projections, and an environment that was appealing to all the senses. Heavily influenced by reading about the “happenings” promoted by the likes of Pink Floyd, Andy Warhol and Velvet Underground, and Ken Kesey’s Merry Pranksters; they envisioned a modern day take of these art “be-ins”, and thus was born the concept of CloudWatch. Created by DJs LoveGrove and Bobble featured guests included: Tom Middleton, Mixmaster Morris, Autechre, Pete Lawrence, Kevin Yost, DJ Spooky, Robert Rich, Steve Roach, Spacetime Continuum, Q-Burn’s Abstract Message, Terre Thaemlitz, Matty Skylab, Thievery Corporation and DJ Wally. FORWARD and the CloudWatch founders are excited to be uniting together to bring this special event back for what promises to be a memorable audio/visual experience, at one of the most unique venues DC has to offer.

item.title: Le Parody
item.dc:creator: avik
item.content:encoded:
Electric beats join hypnotic melodies in Le Parody's music, bursting in a controlled explosion of sounds and references difficult to classify.
Dial your lover's number in a rotary phone. Dance in the cyber-punk future. Black and white movies. Scent of the Pacific and color of the Mediterranean. What best defines Le Parody is that it's almost impossible to define. Their songs are good for a late-night party and for the following slow morning. Their live performances take you on a trip between icy glaciers and burning deserts.
Its very formation is unusual. Andalusian Sole Parody provides the name (stressed on the next-to-last syllable, not like the English word), and acts as the loop composer, ukulele player and voice. Cuban Frank Santiuste's trumpet contributes the measured out, enveloping harmony in this very personal project. Their first work, Cásala (sound track), has become a well-known secret, begged to be heard on all sorts of stages.
Their interest in poetry and their exploration of electronic sounds bringgs Le Parody to the electronic music festival Forward DC 2014, a five-day celebration of electronic creative culture.

item.title: FORWARD 2014 Opening Celebration and A/V Showcase
item.dc:creator: avik
item.content:encoded: FORWARD 2014 is proud to present its opening celebration at the Goethe-Institut of Washington DC. The event is free to enter and enjoy a drink and the sounds of local selectors in the Goethe Institut's gallery. The Gallery will be featuring photos in honor of Blue Note Records 75th anniversary. Blue Note's roots lie in Berlin, where Alfred Lion, a teenager in the thrall of swing music, met Francis (Frank) Wolff, a young photographer with similar musical interests, in 1924. Their mutual love of American jazz fed a strong friendship. Both men moved to New York in the 1930s, where Blue Note Records was born in 1939. In the Goethe Theater International A/V Live acts Grischa Lichtenberger (Berlin) and Helm (London) will be performing alongside Baltimore's A'phreaq and our own [capsaicin] In the Gallery: Silence In Metropolis (Funkdamentalist and Sam Kosh) Jeffrey Prosser (Cavale) Dave Martin (Black Swan Recordings) For more about FORWARD visit: www.forwarddc.com >> FORWARD PASS HOLDERS, PICK UP YOUR PASSES HERE << More about the featured artists: Grischa Lichtenberger ( raster-noton): Grischa Lichtenberger was born in Bielefeld 1983. In 2009 he released his debut EP ~treibgut ununbium on german label Raster-Noton. ~treibgut - a system of references to the river Rhein - operated as a motto for varied expressions: installations, videos, music, painting and drawings. Beginning in 2006, while moving to Düsseldorf, Lichtenberger decided to rethink the artistic process from scratch - it's ethical legitimization and it's epistemological backgrounds - all in regard to the concreteness of the biographical situation in its landscape and history. Since 2008 Grischa Lichtenberger lives in Berlin. With the new "supertitle" andyrchie iv he tries to proceed the idea or revaluating the reference to landscape as "the place we live in". Lichtenberger’s focus is not only the musical expression, but the process of creating art in general. Always regarding the complexity and difficulties of communication and material referenciality, he seeks to overcome the dominance of functional interpretations, while maintaining an open access to technology and production. The archive of samples and fragments of overcome and discarded technological artefacts and everyday livestock is enabled by an ethical figure, wherein art is to address and regard the other, without economizing or confining them. http://www.grischa-lichtenberger.com/ Helm (Alter/Pan) : Helm is Luke Younger - a sound artist and experimental musician based in London, working with a vast array of revolving instrumentation and abstract sound sources. Younger's compositions build a dense aural landscape which touches on aspects of musique concrete, uncomfortable sound poetry, industrial, and hallucinatory drones. To this date, he has produced three full length albums; debut To An End, self released on his own ALTER imprint in 2010, was a complex network of intricate layers and mixed sounds, described by John Elliott (Emeralds / Spectrum Spools) as "a haunting composition of field recordings, tape loops, percussion, and electronics (among other things), creating an extremely tense and daunting audio tapestry which leaves the listener pondering the intense meaning of the sounds chosen". Its follow up, 'Cryptography,' was released a year later on Graham Lambkin's (The Shadow Ring) acclaimed KYE label, consisting of a five-part suite of expertly rendered electro-acoustic study using processed piano, Casio MT-40, cymbal and broken guitar strings. The album received enough acclaim within the underground to sell out its pressing and even made it into The Wire Magazines top 50 albums of 2011, with gigs alongside Mark McGuire, Oneohtrix Point Never and an extensive tour of Europe with Élg and Tomutonttu. For his third album, 2012's 'Impossible Symmetry,' Younger made the move to the PAN label which is where he currently calls home. The album saw Younger moving forward and refining his sound further whilst also marking a new chapter in the Helm canon as being the first to be informed by live performance. Recorded over a year in London with some technical assistance from John Hannon (Liberez), most of the compositions were created out of ideas / improvisations that were conceived in a live context and then turned into finished works in the studio. Whilst being an electronic record primarily, it contained acoustic sound sources used in a similar methodology to Cryptography, and incorporated a more extensive use of electronic elements with moments of rhythmic dark ambience recalling early Coil and Cabaret Voltaire to Traversable Wormhole's industrial minimalism. Younger creates a world where his instruments morph into spectral rust, a shimmering klang swims alongside passive noise and the relationship between acoustic and electronic derived sounds forms a solid foundation.

item.title: FORWARD 2014 Techno Showcase w/ DANIEL BELL aka DBX (Extended Set)

FORWARD 2014 Presents the Techno Showcase featuring DANIEL BELL aka DBX (Extended Set) There are few people in this scene that we enjoy hearing extended sets from/by as much as FORWARD legend Daniel Bell. As we began crafting this year's line-up, with a focus on perspective, Daniel was on top of our list of artists we wanted to include. His influence over the years, his selection, taste and ability to keep his thumb on the latest and greatest have always influenced and inspired us. item.title: FORWARD 2014 - 20 Years of 2Tuff Drum & Bass Showcase
item.dc:creator: avik
item.content:encoded:
FORWARD 2014 teams up with pioneering drum & bass crew 2Tuff to present a special drum & bass showcase. This will also be the next special event of the “20 Years of 2Tuff” campaign where 2Tuff is celebrating 20 years in the game. Please join us as we welcome two of San Francisco's most gifted selectors - Submorphics & Method One along with New York's T.R.A.C. who will be joined by 2Tuff head honcho Slant in addition to Cadence's Illogic & Vanniety Kills. FEATURING:

SUBMORPHICS

Innerground, Hospital, Liquid V, Good Looking, Driven AM >> SAN FRANCISCO https://soundcloud.com/submorphics https://www.facebook.com/Submorphics https://twitter.com/GregSubmorphics

METHOD ONE

31 Records, Secret Operations, Auxiliary >> SAN FRANCISCO https://www.facebook.com/method.one.music https://soundcloud.com/method-one

T.R.A.C.

Liquid V Recordings, Bassdrive >> NYC http://fb.com/tracmuzik https://soundcloud.com/t-r-a-c

SLANT

20 Years of 2Tuff >> DC https://www.facebook.com/slant https://soundcloud.com/dj-slant https://twitter.com/djslant

ILLOGIC & VANNIETY KILLS

Cadence >> DC https://www.facebook.com/cadencedc
9PM - 3AM | 21+ | $8 ADVANCE >> $12 DOOR FREE FOR FORWARD 2014 PASS HOLDERS
GET YOUR FORWARD PASSES HERE: http://www.forwarddc.com/passes.html *REINFORCED SOUND FEATURING THE 88 SOUND SYSTEM*
SUBMORPHICS Submorphics (Greg Axelrad) creates deep ocular future funk, with parts retro soul, Detroit/Chicago synthentics, jazz, film soundtracks and indie vibes infusing his harmonies. Beginning on the humble local scenes of Detroit and Chicago, Submorphics has since DJ’ed in over 40 cities, headlining major gigs at Fabric in London, and across Europe and North America. While he is on the decks, Submorphics sonically alloys disparate styles; the grimy and the smooth, the hypnotic and the astonishing. In the past 7 years his fluid musicality has been embraced by DJs like Fabio, Marky, Bryan Gee, Hype, LTJ Bukem, Bailey and Goldie; with releases “Miles Ahead”, “Step in the Spot ft. Selfsays”, “Mellow Madness”, “Summer Soul” and many more receiving heavy play on BBC Radio One and clubs internationally. Celebrated primarily for his soulful drum and bass sounds, Submorphics has diversified his repertoire, publishing a plethora of emotive and bass-heavy music in the 100-140 bpm range. The eclectic musician has also taken on the role of producer for vocalists Armanni Reign and Christina Tamayo. Submorphics exploded into 2012 with the release of the anthemic Camo & Krooked- Change Me (Submorphics Remix) on Hospital Records. Subsequently, deep and soulful releases on Drum & Bass Arena, Rubik and Influenza added to his impressive discography.
METHOD ONE In the twenty years since he first started experimenting with sampled loops, Jason Leder aka Method One has become one of the elder statesmen of the American drum and bass scene. As a dj, he has honed his craft through hundreds of gigs stretching back to the early nineties, and can be heard every other Sunday on www.bassdrive.com. As a musician, he is responsible for numerous releases and remixes on labels such as Auxiliary, 31 Records, Levitated, Secret Operations, Vampire, Absys, Covert Operations, Vibez, Red Mist, Offworld, Nexus (Good Looking), Testflight, Elektra/Warner Brothers and more. Jason lives in San Francisco, California.
T.R.A.C. Hailing from Brooklyn, New York, T.R.A.C. Is demonstrative of the borough's rich history of lyrical prowess. As a staple in both the drum & bass and underground hip-hop scenes of New York, he has been a consistent presence on the microphone since 1997. His repertoire features work with both legendary and pioneering artists including LTJ Bukem, Roni Size, Paul Sg, and Goldie. His lyrical vocabulary allows him to walk the line between genres, garnering him acclamation for his bluesy hiphop efforts to crowd-rocking drum and bass accompaniment. T.R.A.C. Made his solo debut on BBE Records with the Network, fully produced by 4hero's Marc Mac.  OE4 magazine gave the project a 6-star rating. Other projects include Visioneers Hipology and This Is That on Omniverse Records. T.R.A.C. has also worked with international artists, teaming up with UK's Lewis Parker on both Lewis Parker's Home Grown Hip Hop to his recent 2013 critically acclaimed The Glass Ceiling. Most recently, he has dropped singles with Jazzsticks/Goodlooking artist Paul Sg. In September of 2013, they released Strive which reached top 3 on the Juno singles charts. This led to being featured and hosting on Liquid V’s Club Sessions compilation (Vol.5). T.R.A.C. teamed up with Paul Sg once again on Let Me Show, a soulful liquid song fueled by T.R.A.C.'s uplifting lyrics and La Meduza’s sultry voice. Both songs are currently respected and spun by locals and DJs abroad. As momentum keeps building, be sure to check his music and catch him in action. Whether Hip Hop or Drum & Bass, T.R.A.C. has proven himself to be a true talent and like a fire, there seems to be more and more catching on to him. Indeed!

item.title: FORWARD Presents Exclusive Screening of : I Dream of Wires
item.dc:creator: avik
item.content:encoded: FORWARD is proud to announce that it will be among the select music festivals worldwide hosting a screening of the film I Dream of Wires. The screening will be held at the Goethe-Institut in Washington, DC on Thursday, May 15th at 7pm, with a running time of 93 minutes.   The film premiered at Moogfest, and will now be screened in very limited release at pioneering music festivals worldwide in May, including:  CIMMfest — Chicago, IL; Together Fest — Boston, MA; Bio Rio — Stockholm, Sweden; and Ikonst — Malmö, Sweden. Tickets: $8/12:  FREE for FORWARD pass holders "I Dream of Wires" (IDOW) is an independent documentary film about the phenomenal resurgence of the modular synthesizer — exploring the passions, obsessions and dreams of people who have dedicated part of their lives to this esoteric electronic music machine. IDOW is written and directed by Robert Fantinatto with Jason Amm (Ghostly International recording artist Solvent) serving as producer and co-writer. Inventors, musicians and enthusiasts are interviewed about their relationship with the modular synthesizer — for many, it’s an all-consuming passion. Established musicians such as Trent Reznor (Nine Inch Nails), Carl Craig and John Foxx show off their systems and explain why they opt to use this volatile but ultimately rewarding technology. Meanwhile, a new generation of dance and electronica artists including Clark, James Holden and Factory Floor explain why they’ve stepped away from laptops to embrace the sound and physicality of modular synthesizers. Innovative companies like Modcan and Doepfer, driven by a desire to revive modular synthesizers, discuss how they planted the seeds that have now grown into a major cottage industry. What started out as a “vintage-revival scene” in the ’90s has grown into an underground phenomena with a growing market of modular obsessives craving ever more wild and innovative sounds and interfaces. Today, the modular synthesizer is no longer an esoteric curiosity or even a mere music instrument — it is an essential tool for radical new sounds and a bonafide subculture. Interview subjects include musicians and producers Morton Subotnick, Bernie Krause, Gary Numan, Chris Carter (Throbbing Gristle), Daniel Miller, Flood, Trent Reznor (Nine Inch Nails), Carl Craig, cEvin Key (Skinny Puppy), James Holden, Factory Floor, Legowelt, John Foxx and Vince Clarke, as well as manufacturers and modular industry leaders Doepfer, Modcan, Make Noise, Intellijel, Metasonix, Synthesis Technology/MOTM, Muffwiggler Mike and Andreas Schneider. Trailer: *Please note that the trailer references a 4 Hour “Hardcore Edition” director’s cut. FORWARD will be screening the official theatrical version with a running time of 93 minutes.  A theatrical trailer was unavailable at the time of announcement. I Dream of Wires Website: http://www.idreamofwires.org/ Reviews: Synthopia: http://www.synthtopia.com/content/2013/08/05/i-dream-of-wires-the-modular-documentary-review/ Waveformless: http://waveformless.blogspot.com/2013/08/i-dream-of-wires-exclusive-review-and.html Music Radar: http://www.musicradar.com/us/news/tech/i-dream-of-wires-a-new-modular-synth-documentary-571118

item.title: Omar S.
item.dc:creator: avik
item.content:encoded: Detroit's Omar-S (Alex Omar Smith; aka DJ Snotburger, DJ Snotinburg) emerged in 2003 as an underground techno/house maverick, releasing rigidly funky productions, made with analog gear, on his FXHE label. Though his 12" releases were pressed in small quantities with handwritten labels (and with run-out etchings like "Techno music is my heritage -- techno is not dead DAMN IT!" and "Thanks to Rick Wilhite -- I know I get on your nerves"), it wasn't long before his releases reached specialty shops in the U.K. and Germany. Though he was building a cult following and was often placed by writers within the same context as fellow Detroit natives Moodymann and Theo Parrish, it wasn't until 2009 that he truly strayed from his low-profile, self-sufficient mode. Parrish's Sound Signature label released his "Blown Valvetrane" 12", and shortly after that, Smith provided the 45th mix for London club Fabric's self-named mix series. The majority of Smith's output was released on vinyl, but he also has full-length CD titles to his credit, including 2004'sCollaborating (billed as Oasis, co-produced by Smith and the possibly nonexistent Shadow Ray) and 2005's Just Ask the Lonely. The latter was reissued on FXHE in 2009.

item.title: Le Parody at FORWARD DC 2014
item.dc:creator: avik
item.content:encoded:
Join us for the concert of Le Parody at Tropicalia in Washington DC, as part of the electronic music festival Forward DC, a five-day celebration of electronic creative culture. This will be the second stop of their US tour, that will take them to Centro Cultural Español de Cooperación Iberoamericana in Miami on May 15, and to Bowery Poetry Club on May 16 in New York among other places. Their first work, Cásala (sound track), has become a well-known secret, begged to be heard on all sorts of stages. Electric beats join hypnotic melodies in Le Parody's music, bursting in a controlled explosion of sounds and references difficult to classify. Its very formation is unusual. Andalusian Sole Parody provides the name (stressed on the next-to-last syllable, not like the English word), and acts as the loop composer, ukulele player and voice. Cuban Frank Santiuste's trumpet contributes the measured out, enveloping harmony in this very personal project. Enjoy their music here: http://leparody.bandcamp.com/

ADMISSION IS FREE. Don't miss it!

item.title: About
item.dc:creator: user
item.content:encoded: The world is a topsy turvy, complicated and at times very confusing place. Sometimes it’s hard to stay sane amidst the varying news, opinions and attitudes we’re bombarded with on a daily basis. As we engage with the world, our friends, families, colleagues and the overall day-to-day we started to appreciate and focus on the importance of Perspective. The importance of maintaining perspective in dealing with people and issues; The power that perspective can gift us in addressing a situation, a problem or in analyzing a result can be the difference maker in coming up with the best solution or realization. To that end, Perspective is the artistic, inspirational theme informing this year's FORWARD 2014.

item.title: Forward Preview Event: Amir Alexander
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
FORWARD Preview Event Announcement: A Tribute to Frankie Knuckles and Celebration of the Underground, featuring Amir Alexander.
 
 
FORWARD and Bump ‘n Grind are happy to welcome Amir Alexander to Zeba for his DC Debut. Amir currently lives in Berlin, but is and has been a mainstay and proponent of the Chicago underground house scene for years. As proponents of the underground for over 10 years in DC thinking through our Frankie Knuckles tribute and FORWARD’s perspective theme, we couldn’t ask for a better figure/guide to help us celebrate Frankie’s legacy than Amir. Frankie pioneered the underground in Chicago, creating a scene and lifestyle for thousands where the literally wasn’t one. He created a refuge for those that walked on the fringe, those that needed a safe place to express themselves emotionally/physically for hours on end. Amir is carrying that torch, carrying that flame and will be showcasing and juxtaposing the Chicago underground’s legacy and perspective via three turntables for our beloved DC community. Bring your open mind and heart. Wear those shoes and duds that inspire you to move and prepare to shimmy your way across that baby powdered dance floor as we welcome Amir Alexander to DC. FREE for FORWARD 2014 Pass holders. FB Event » Here «

item.title: Andy Grant Provides the Fourth Installment to our Perspective Mix Series
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
With UK roots, Andy Grant has been holding down vinyl, house music culture in DC for a while now via DC House Grooves. He put together a really nice mix for our Perspective Series, that we’re happy to share with you today. In his own words:
"For the last few weeks I’ve been trying to figure out how I would do a mix with the theme 'perspective.'  I knew I didn’t want to offer up just another mix of the latest dance floor bangers, but apart from that I just didn’t have a clue. My process for recording a mix is first to spend a few hours, or even days, listening to records and putting together a pile of 'candidate' records, which may or may not be used. The next step is to find some time to record when I know I will not be disturbed, so I can get behind the decks and take care of business. I never plan a set or a mix; I just put the first record on and see what happens, letting each tune provide the inspiration for the next. For this mix I used a stack of tunes that I had cast aside in previous listening sessions. Most of these were records that hadn’t made the cut for previous gigs, mixes and radio shows, but were just begging to be played.  I found the right time, hit the record button put a record on and went with the flow.  Fortunately the time was right, I got into the zone, and this was the result. Listening to the mix for the first time I couldn’t believe these records hadn’t made the cut before. Great music is all about perspective, and more often than not the records that stand the test of time are the ones that don’t jump out at you at first, the ones that take some time to get into.  This mix captures a collection of those records in a unique context, casting them in a new light, providing a new perspective." - Andy Grant

Download Andy Grant: Perspective Mix 004

Track List

1. Reno Wurzbacher – The Love You Got (Sven Weisemann Closeness Mix) (Colombage) 2. Levon Vincent – These Games (Novel Sounds) 3. Rising Sun – Lift Up Your Faces (Sven’s in Da Face Mix) 4. Blue Base – Blue Base (Paper Boys Remix) (Bush) 5. Jeremy – Where the Heart Is (Driftwood) 6. Brad P – Take U There (Inner Shift Music) 7. Hiver – Zefiro (Vidab) 8. Theo Parish – Lost Angel (Music Is…) 9. Duijn & Douglas – Eddie’s Groove (Aybee’s Re:shuffle) (Feelharmonic) 10. Vakula – Fifth Experiment (Bandura) 11. BLM – Range Mod (Contrast Wax) 12. Move D – Happylock (Endless Flight) 13. Levon Vincent – Deeper (Novel Sounds) 14. DJ Sprinkles – Midtown 120 Blues (Endless Flight) 15. Tuccillo – Introduciendo (Holic Trax) 16. item.title: FORWARD 2014 Artist Announcement : Mr. Saturday Night
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: FORWARD 2014 is inspired by Perspective. One way that will be manifesting itself in our programming is through nights that focus on a particular artist or label. Allowing them the opportunity to share with the FORWARD community, their perspective on sound/aesthetic/energy - a party. The first entity we’re excited to share with you that will be featured at FORWARD 2014 is Justin Carter and Eamon Harkin of Mr. Saturday Night. The first time we met Justin and Eamon was quite a few years back. We had hosted Kyle Hall on Saturday night here (his 18th birthday) in DC and they were hosting him at their infamous outdoor Sunday party at Gowanus Grove aka BKLYN Yard. What a party. The global dance community was there shaking their tail feather, having a chat, train spotting, taking in the scene and energy. White, Black, Thick, Thin, Hip, Weird, Gay, Straight…just the way we like it. Since then, the guys were featured heavily in Resident Advisor’s Real Scene’s NYC (as well as label mates and FORWARD alumn Archie Pelago) - have gone on to tour the world and start a record label while still holding down their regular no BS, mission driven DIY events. We’re thrilled to be bringing our NY bretheren and the Mr. Saturday Night vibe to our beloved FORWARD community for their DC Debut.

item.title: FORWARD Perspective Mix Part 5: CHADWICK
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
We’re thrilled to share with you the 5th edition of our exclusive 'Perspective' Mix Series brought to you by longtime DC selector and current Flash Resident: Chadwick. He’s been a skilled technician since the glory days of the 90’s & 2000’s and has inspired many of our favorite area DJs to dedicate themselves to their craft. A truly versatile DJ that has a reputation for curatuing sets with an acute attention to detail, we’re honored to present Chadwick Wilson’s ‘Prescriptive Perspectives’ Mix. "Prescriptive Perspectives" is about what often becomes my favorite part of going out: The after party. The after-after party. The waning hours of a fun night. Time spent with friends new and old and opportunities to share favorite records from my collection. Songs that don’t really need to be mixed because the conversation creates the playlist. House, rock, reggae, and vintage sound effects LPs, anything goes during these hours. While thumbing through the shelves to find THAT ONE, it’s a non-stop flood of memories. The people, places and parties all defined by the playing of each record. Simultaneously, new memories are created and now someone else can say “THAT song, THAT morning when…” I hope you enjoy the mix and it someday finds the right time in one of your mornings. — Chadwick, April 2014

item.title: FORWARD Announces Screening of ‘I Dream Of Wires’
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: FORWARD is proud to announce that it will be among the select music festivals worldwide hosting a screening of the film I Dream of Wires. The screening will be held at the Goethe-Institut in Washington, DC on Thursday, May 15th at 7pm, with a running time of 93 minutes.   The film premiered at Moogfest, and will now be screened in very limited release at pioneering music festivals worldwide in May, including:  CIMMfest — Chicago, IL; Together Fest — Boston, MA; Bio Rio — Stockholm, Sweden; and Ikonst — Malmö, Sweden. Tickets: $8/12:  FREE for FORWARD pass holders "I Dream of Wires" (IDOW) is an independent documentary film about the phenomenal resurgence of the modular synthesizer — exploring the passions, obsessions and dreams of people who have dedicated part of their lives to this esoteric electronic music machine. IDOW is written and directed by Robert Fantinatto with Jason Amm (Ghostly International recording artist Solvent) serving as producer and co-writer. Inventors, musicians and enthusiasts are interviewed about their relationship with the modular synthesizer — for many, it’s an all-consuming passion. Established musicians such as Trent Reznor (Nine Inch Nails), Carl Craig and John Foxx show off their systems and explain why they opt to use this volatile but ultimately rewarding technology. Meanwhile, a new generation of dance and electronica artists including Clark, James Holden and Factory Floor explain why they’ve stepped away from laptops to embrace the sound and physicality of modular synthesizers. Innovative companies like Modcan and Doepfer, driven by a desire to revive modular synthesizers, discuss how they planted the seeds that have now grown into a major cottage industry. What started out as a “vintage-revival scene” in the ’90s has grown into an underground phenomena with a growing market of modular obsessives craving ever more wild and innovative sounds and interfaces. Today, the modular synthesizer is no longer an esoteric curiosity or even a mere music instrument — it is an essential tool for radical new sounds and a bonafide subculture. Interview subjects include musicians and producers Morton Subotnick, Bernie Krause, Gary Numan, Chris Carter (Throbbing Gristle), Daniel Miller, Flood, Trent Reznor (Nine Inch Nails), Carl Craig, cEvin Key (Skinny Puppy), James Holden, Factory Floor, Legowelt, John Foxx and Vince Clarke, as well as manufacturers and modular industry leaders Doepfer, Modcan, Make Noise, Intellijel, Metasonix, Synthesis Technology/MOTM, Muffwiggler Mike and Andreas Schneider. Trailer: *Please note that the trailer references a 4 Hour “Hardcore Edition” director’s cut. FORWARD will be screening the official theatrical version with a running time of 93 minutes.  A theatrical trailer was unavailable at the time of announcement. I Dream of Wires Website: http://www.idreamofwires.org/ Reviews: Synthopia: http://www.synthtopia.com/content/2013/08/05/i-dream-of-wires-the-modular-documentary-review/ Waveformless: http://waveformless.blogspot.com/2013/08/i-dream-of-wires-exclusive-review-and.html Music Radar: http://www.musicradar.com/us/news/tech/i-dream-of-wires-a-new-modular-synth-documentary-571118

item.title: FORWARD Announces Two FREE Daytime events at The Jefferson Memorial
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
FORWARD is humbled and honored to be able to share our culture in one of the most historic sites in our country - The Jefferson Memorial. It also happens to be one of our favorite vistas of the city that we were born in, work in and love. On Saturday and Sunday May 17th and 18th, from 12pm - 8:30pm on the Tidal Basin facing steps of The Jefferson Memorial, FORWARD will present two days of music and dance celebrating community and electronic creative culture. On Saturday, our friends from Chuck Levins Washington Music Center will be bringing a bunch of controllers and synths for folks to play with. For more information visit » Here « Our friends at Bump n Grind will be providing free coffee while supplies last! We’ve been working towards this day for over 3 years and have curated a special line-up of talent that showcases the depth of our Community, and are excited about the significance of this opportunity. The days will feature people that pioneered our local scene like Sam “The Man” Burns and Lovegrove, as well as National/International Legend King Britt who has been holding it down in and representing North America for years. We’re also happy to feature longtime collaborator and friend Robert Manos who will be debuting his soulful new Live set. Joining them are musical stalwarts in our scene, people who’ve been hosting events, artists and nurturing various aspects and corners of our community for over 5 years. The final feather in the weekend cap includes long-time collaborator Baltimore Aerial Dance and west-coast sister LeiLei DeKirby. We currently have a fundraising campaign to help us with these free/public components of FORWARD. Please help us if you can, any amount makes a difference! Visit » HERE « Can you tell we’re excited? Enough said! We hope that you will join us for what promises to be a memorable, epic day. It’s hard to imagine that we will be playing music, dancing, picnicking, hanging out with Thomas Jefferson looking over our shoulders - while looking at the Franklin Delano Roosevelt and Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. Memorials; The White House and Smithsonian across the Tidal Basin.

SEE YOU SATURDAY AND SUNDAY AT THE JEFFERSON!
